<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-15T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-15T15:00:00-05:00" n="719" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d719">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/1607c: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-15T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 15,
                                            1920—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>What is extent and influence of the authority exercised in Chinese
                                Eastern Railroad zone by Russian Consul over and above his functions
                                as a Russian Consul on Chinese territory and what are his official
                                connections with the railroad? What are his views as to (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) Japanese (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)
                                Semenov (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>) control of the railroad?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>